ðŸ§Š What is a Node?

A node is:

a physical or virtual machine

where Kubernetes is installed

a worker machine

where containers actually run

Historical note:

previously called minions

If a node fails, the applications running on it go down â€” so we need more than one node.

ðŸ§© What is a Kubernetes Cluster?

A cluster is:

a group of nodes working together

Benefits:

high availability (if one fails, others keep running)

